<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Steels Taks Second Consecutive Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Belgian Tom Steels claimed back-to-
back victories in the Tour de France with a decisive sprint at the
end of Tuesday's third stage over 194.5 kms from Nantes, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
Steels beat off Germany's Erik Zabel and Australian Stuart O'
Grady for his sixth Tour stage triumph, lifting him to second
overall, 11 seconds behind race leader Jaan Kirsipuu of Estonia.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian's second placing at Challans behind Kirsipuu on
Sunday was followed by revenge 24 hours later when he edged out
Kirsipuu at St. Nazaire.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's stage featured a breakaway which lasted 121
kilometres before Frenchman Frederic Guesdon, winner of the 1997
Paris-Roubaix classic, and first-year professional Massimo Giunti
of Italy were overhauled.  
</P>
</TEXT>
