<HEADLINE> Hillary Clinton Forms Exploratory Committee For </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- U.S. First Lady Hillary Rodham
Clinton Tuesday formed an exploratory committee to a race for a
Senate seat in New York.
</P>
<P>
"This morning we filed a statement of organization with the
Federal Election Commission to establish the Hillary Rodham
Clinton for U.S. Senate Exploratory Committee," her campaign
spokesman Howard Wolfson said.
</P>
<P>
Wolfson announced that Hillary Clinton will begin a summerlong
listening tour of New York tomorrow at a farm.
</P>
<P>
"Over the next month Mrs. Clinton will travel throughout the
state, meeting with New Yorkers in small groups and listening to
them discuss the issues that concern them most, " the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
Formation of the exploratory committee will allow the first
lady to raise and spend money in preparation for the race for the
Democratic nomination.
</P>
<P>
Hillary Clinton, the only first lady to run for public office,
is expected to compete with New York City Mayor Rudolph Giuliani
on the Republican side in the race for the New York Senate seat.
</P>
<P>
Jiuliani has already formed a Senate exploratory committee and
raised almost three million dollars toward the race.  
</P>
</TEXT>
