<HEADLINE> African Social Security Summit to Be Held in Ghana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The 13th summit of the African
member states of the International Social Security Association is
due to be held in Ghana from July 13 to 16 this year, the
Ethiopian Social Security authority announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The four-day meeting, jointly organized by the International
Social Security Association and the Ghanaian National Social
Security Institute, would deliberate, among others, on ways of
improving the quality of social security services in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The International Social Security Association, which has 362
members, conducts researches and offers training aimed at
bolstering social security services around the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
