<HEADLINE> Russian Prime Minister to Visit Washington </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei
Stepashin will hold talks with U.S. Vice President Al Gore at the
end of the month to seek American cooperation for Russia's
economy, Gore's office said on Tuesday in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The visit, scheduled on July 27, will be the first for
Stepashin as the Russian prime minister and the first meeting in a
year of the U.S.-Russian Joint Commission on Economic and
Technological Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Stepashin, who has talked several times with Gore on the
telephone, is due to bring with him government economic
specialists and visit American corporations, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the U.S.-Russian Joint Commission was useful
in helping the two sides to "expand our areas of agreement and
open channels we can draw on during periods of disagreement."
</P>
<P>
The commission meeting was originally scheduled in March. And
Former Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov was on his way to
Washington for the occasion in March when he turned around his jet
and went home to protest Washington's decision to launch bombing
campaign against Yugoslavia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
