<HEADLINE> Top-seed Hrbaty Beaten by Tarango </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 6 (Xinhua) -- American Jeff Tarango produced a
surprise vicotry after defeating top-seed Dominik Hrbaty of
Slovakia 6-1, 6-2 Tuesday, in the opening round of the Swedish
Open held in Bastad.
</P>
<P>
Second-seed Thomas Johansson of Sweden edged Spain's Alberto
Berasategui 6-3, 1-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Tarango and David Adams of South Africa are the top-seeded team
in the doubles event. On Monday, they defeated Alberto Berasategui
and Francisco Roig of Spain in straight sets.
</P>
<P>
Berasategui's compatriot, German Puentes, knocked out No. 8
seed Jan Kroslak of Slovakia, 4-6, 6-1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Wild card Nicklas Kulti of Sweden also advanced to the second
round, despite dropping the first set against Michael Kohlmann of
Germany. Kulti won 1-6, 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
21-year-old Markus Hipfl of Austria upset No. 7 seed Gaston
Gaudio of Argentina 6-3, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's other action, Hernan Gumy of Argentina eliminated
Italian Davide Sanguinetti 6-2, 6-1, while No. 6 seed Christian
Ruud of Norway defeated Swedish qualifier Johan Ortegren 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
</TEXT>
