<HEADLINE> Greece Hopes EU Not to Change Decision on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Greece on Tuesday expressed the hope
that the European Union (EU) would not change its decision to base
its agency for the Balkan reconstruction in the northern Greek
city of Thessaloniki.
</P>
<P>
The decision taken by the 15 EU members in Rio De Janeiro,
Brazil, would not be changed, Greek government spokesman Dimitris
Reppas said at a press briefing.
</P>
<P>
On the sidelines of the EU and Latin American summit which took
place in Rio De Janeiro, Brazil, later June, EU leaders decided to
base its agency for the Balkan reconstruction in Thessaloniki.
Greece has voiced its satisfaction with the EU decision, saying
that such a decision has proved that Greece could play a role in
economic and peaceful development in the Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
While confirming that there were "circles in the EU" trying to
move the agency to Pristina, capital of the Yugoslav province of
Kosovo, Reppas stressed that Greece would respond in a convincing
manner to those opposed to the choice of Thessaloniki.
</P>
<P>
Since the end of the war in Yugoslavia triggered by the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), Greece has tried hard to play
a major role in regional reconstruction, and suggested that
Thessaloniki, the largest city in northern Greece, be chosen as a
center for EU services for reconstruction in the Balkans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
