<HEADLINE> Fischer Supports for Middle East Peace Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 6 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Joschka
Fischer assured on Tuesday in Bonn the new Israeli Foreign
Minister, David Levy, of Germany's support in its efforts to
secure a peace settlement in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
In a best-wishes message, Fischer said that the expectations of
the new government under new prime minister Ehud Barak were high.
</P>
<P>
"In Israel and the entire region, as well as in Germany, (the
rest of) Europe and worldwide, people are hoping for new impulses
to overcome the stalled peace process and to smooth the way to a
long-lasting and just peace," he said.
</P>
<P>
Levy has already served as foreign minister twice, most
recently in the government of Benjamin Netanyahu which ended with
his resignation in January 1998 in a bitter feud with Netanyahu
over various issues including the bogged-down peace process.
</P>
</TEXT>
