<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus to See British Tourists Influx in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A record 1.1 million British
tourists are expected to visit Cyprus this year, up by 10 percent
over last year, the Cyprus News Agency reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the London-based office of the Cyprus
Tourism Organization show 2.22 million British tourists visited
Cyprus, a 6.4 percent increase over 1997.
</P>
<P>
At the end of 1998, there were 4,344 tourist accommodation
units in operation in Cyprus with a total capacity of 86,151 beds.
</P>
<P>
Britain remained as a major source of tourism to Cyprus in
1998, with a share of 45.7 percent in the island's tourist traffic.
</P>
<P>
Germany ranked the second with 9.4 percent, followed by Russia
with 7.9 percent, Sweden 5.1 percent, Switzerland 3.8 percent and
Greece 3.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is the main foreign currency earner of Cyprus, which
contributes 20 percent of the country's gross national product
(GNP). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
