<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's PC Sales to Rise 32 Percent This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The sales of personal computers in
Thailand are estimated to increase by 32 percent in volume this
year compared with 1998, according to a report of the research
company IDC Thailand available on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The company projected that the PC shipments in Thailand will
reach 243,091 units this year, or 329.5 million U.S. dollars in
value. The PC sales in Thailand last year were recorded at 184,146
units with a value of 245.9 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The significant growth in PC demand in Thailand has been
contributed by the government's information technology and
educational projects and the use of PCs in small and medium-size
companies, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The sales of personal computers in the second quarter of this
year also witnessed a growth rate of 11 percent compared with the
same quarter of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
