<HEADLINE> Repatriated Eritreans Arrive Home From Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Eritrean Foreign Ministry said
Tuesday that 1,410 Eritrean civilians repatriated from Ethiopia
arrived at Eritrea' s Red Sea port city of Assab early Monday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The Eritreans and the Ethiopians of Eritrean origin came
through the Burie front line 70 kilometers west of Assab, the
ministry said in a news release available here.
</P>
<P>
A large number of the people had lived their entire life in
Ethiopia and carried Ethiopian passports, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The release said Monday's arrival of Eritreans was thought to
be only the first batch of some 15,000 Eritreans who remain
destitute in Ethiopia and will be repatriated in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
So far, Eritrea have received 60,000 Eritreans repatriated from
Ethiopia on their ethnicity, the ministry added.
</P>
<P>
There is no immediate comment from the Ethiopian side on the
repatriation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
