<HEADLINE> Greece Continues Nationwide Crackdown on Illegal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Greece on Tuesday continued its
nationwide crackdown on illegal immigrants with the aim of
combating crime as well as providing a clear picture of how many
foreigners were legally in the country.
</P>
<P>
The crackdown on illegal immigrants comes after a meeting of
the Greek government Council on Foreign Affairs and Defense on
Friday, which decided to hire more than 2,500 more police officers
and border guards in a bid to curb illegal immigration in Greece.
</P>
<P>
In Attica province, Greek police detained about 500 suspected
illegal immigrants, mostly Albanians, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Police said that those found to have legitimate residence
permits would be released while those who are found to be in
Greece illegally would be deported.
</P>
<P>
50,000 illegal immigrants have been deported from Greece since
the beginning of this year, according to official data issued by
Greece's Public Order Ministry.  
</P>
