<HEADLINE> French Population Attains More Than 60 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The entire population in France has
attained 60,082,000 by the end of March 1999, which shows an
average 0.38 percent growth per year since 1990, said the French
State Statistics and Economics Study Institute (INSEE) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The number of people living in France's mainland accounts for
58,416,500, while that of overseas territories is 1,665,500, said
INSEE.
</P>
<P>
