<HEADLINE> Algeria's Population Hits 29.2 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The population of Algeria hit 29.2
million in 1998, said statistics released Tuesday by the Algerian
National Department for Statistics (NDS).
</P>
<P>
The population stood at 22.7 million in 1987, the Algerian News
Agency quoted the census as saying. It put the annual growth rate
of population during this period at 2.28 percent.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate from 1977 to 1987 stood at 3.06 percent and
at 3.12 percent from 1966 to 1977, said the NDS.
</P>
<P>
Almost 80.8 percent of the population are centered in major
residential areas. The percentage was estimated at 56.1 percent in
1966, 61.2 percent in 1977 and 70.8 percent in 1987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
