<HEADLINE> OAU Restructuring to Improve Efficiency: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 6 (Xinhua)-- The restructuring program of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU), which will cost 19 million
U.S. dollars, will make it a more efficient and influential
organization in the continent, an OAU official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 600-member organization will get thinner by at least 200
positions, Ibrahim Dagash, spokesman of the organization, said at
a news briefing on the discussion of African ambassadors meeting
here.
</P>
<P>
The 18-month-long restructuring program of the OAU, which is to
be carried out among both professionals and non-professionals, is
scheduled to complete by the end of 2000.
</P>
<P>
Dagash said that the restructuring will affect all members of
staff except the positions of secretary-general and his five
senior assistants.
</P>
<P>
The Addis Ababa-based organization has lately been criticized
for low efficiency and overstaff, making it difficult in the
crisis-ridden continent which demands an efficient and influential
continental body for peace and development, some critics say.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1963, the OAU has been devoted to the safeguarding
of independence, unity and promotion of development in the
continent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
