<HEADLINE> Uganda, Rwanda Strengthen Coop in Electricity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Uganda and Rwanda have signed a
bilateral agreement here to implement the second phase of
exchanging electricity supply in fulfilment of regional
integration between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Radio Uganda said in a report Monday that a series of
meetings have been going on toward the speedy implementation of
the second phase.
</P>
<P>
Under this phase, power inter-connection will be via Mbarara
sub-station in Uganda and Gikondo sub-station in Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Uganda and Rwanda also considered the
terms of reference for the construction of the 132/110KV
transmission line from Mbarara to Gikondo as well as the financing
requirements. 
