<HEADLINE> London Stocks Finish at Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON July 6 (Xinhua) - London's leading shares rose to record
high Tuesday on a boost from unexpectedly strong economic data and
a strengthening trend on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 closed up 28.6 points, or 0.43 percent, to finish
at a record 6620.6, as the market shrugged off the interest rate
implications of a surprise 0.2 percent rise in May manufacturing
output and focused on the rosier economic outlook.
</P>
<P>
The report was seen as removing hopes of a further interest
rate cut when the Bank of England's rate committee meets Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Technology stocks are highly concentrated in the wider FTSE 250
index, helping it add 35.8 points, or 0.6 percent, to 6010.8. That
was also a record closing high, beating the 5975 from earlier this
month.
</P>
<P>
Strategists, impressed by the FTSE 100's showing this week,
said the performance over the next few days could determine the
market's success for the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the Xetra Dax finished down 12.72 points at
5612.90, a loss of 0.23 percent. The market was unimpressed by a
smaller-than-expected rise in May unemployment.
</P>
<P>
French stocks were little changed on Tuesday after early
attempts at deeper consolidation were derailed by brisk trade in
oil stocks.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark CAC-40 ended down just 5.23, or 0.11 percent, at
4692.51, paring most of its earlier losses just before the close.
</P>
