During its reforms, China has made policies independently and
managed to maintain political and social stability, an example
which Tanzania should learn from, Mkapa said at his official
residence here while meeting the outgoing Chinese ambassador Zhang
Hongxi.
</P>
<P>
The president said China's achievements from its reforms
impressed him a lot while he visited the country last April.
</P>
<P>
To learn from China's experiences, Tanzania's Minister of
Industries and Commerce Iddi Simba will visit the economic
development zone in Shanghai soon, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Hongxi, who was bidding a farewell to the president, said
that China attaches great importance to its traditional friendship
with Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral relationship between the two nations has strengthened
during the past two years with exchanges of high-level government
officials, Mkapa said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese ambassador said the bilateral relationship has
turned a new chapter after China and Tanzania started to establish
joint ventures as a form of economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa expressed gratitude to China's long-term assistance and
said Tanzania wishes to set up more joint ventures with China.
</P>
<P>
He also said Tanzania will take measures to solve problems
facing the first joint venture between the two countries, the
Tanzania-China Friendship Textile Co. Ltd., which was launched in
April of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Tanzanian president stressed that the two
countries should carry out institutional cooperation involving the
private sector. 
