<HEADLINE> Aircraft Carrier Roosevelt Back to Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Defense Secretary William
Cohen has ordered the aircraft carrier Theodore Roosevelt to
take the place of the aircraft carrier Kitty Hawk in the Persian
Gulf, the Pentagon said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Roosevelt is due to arrive in the Gulf by this weekend,
Pentagon spokesman Ken Bacon said. The carrier has been in the
Mediterranean since April as part of the NATO force that staged
barbarous bombing against Yugoslavia for 11 weeks.
</P>
<P>
The Roosevelt and its battle group originally were assigned
to the Gulf but were diverted when the NATO air bombing broke
out.
</P>
<P>
The Kitty Hawk then rushed to the Gulf in April to fill the
gap left by the Roosevelt. The Kitty Hawk will be back in Asia
within a few weeks, officials here said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
