<DOCNO> XIE19990707.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Loan to Turk Eximbank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved Tuesday
253.5 million U.S. dollars to finance an Export Financial
Intermediation Loan (EFIL) to the Turk Eximbank, backed by a
guarantee from the government of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Turk Eximbank will on-lend the proceeds of this loan to private
exporters through eligible participating private banks, the World
Bank said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The EFIL will provide short- and medium-term working capital
and investment finance to private exporting enterprises to assist
the Turkish exporting sector, hurt by the recent global financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
The loan will also enable a strategic dialogue and close
interaction with the major banks and the Bankers Association in
Turkey. This will be accomplished through setting up a stricter
and upgraded prudential eligibility criteria and banking standards
for capital adequacy, foreign exchange exposure, connected and
insider lending, and risk management systems, the World Bank said.
</P>
<P>
The loan will also further institutional development of the
Turk Eximbank itself as an efficient and professionally-run export
finance institution/export credit agency.
</P>
<P>
The loan has a maturity of seven years, including a three-year
grace period, at the bank's LIBOR-based single-currency rate for
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
