<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Move Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks moved lower
Tuesday on profit-taking.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 4.12 at 11,135.12.
The blue chip index rose 72.82 at the record closing high of
11,139.24 last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The market was closed Monday for the July 4 holiday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly lower. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index fell 3.10 at 1,388.12 and the technology heavy
Nasdaq index fell 4.24 at 2,736.78.
</P>
<P>
The stocks fell Tuesday as investors sold off shares to lock in
profits from last week's big gains. The Dow alone rose 586.68
points or 5.55 percent in the five consecutive sessions last week.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 0.35 at 654.77. But the American
Stock Exchange index rose 2.47 at 804.89 and the Russell 2000
index of smaller companies rose 0.04 at 456.55.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 10-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,609 down, 1,463 up and 489
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 718.47 million shares from 583.75
million in the previous session. 
</P>
