<HEADLINE> Italy Voices Confidence in Finnish Presidency of EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Italy looks with "great sympathy and
confidence" to the six-month duty presidency of the European Union
(EU) of Finland in the conviction that progress can be made on
major EU issues, Italian Premier Massimo D'Alema told his Finnish
counterpart, Paavo Lipponen, here Tuesday.
</P>
