- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUANDA -- The Russian Embassy in Luanda said Tuesday that the
Russian government has called upon the Angolan rebel movement
UNITA to release the Russian crew members of the two planes downed
in northeastern Angola.
</P>
<P>
The embassy said in a press release that the Russian Foreign
Ministry issued a statement in Moscow Tuesday demanding that the
National Union for Total Independence of Angola (UNITA), and its
leader Jonas Savimbi in particular, to take necessary steps to
enable the pilots to return home. (Angola-Russian Pilots)
</P>
