President Hafez al-Assad visited Moscow for the first time since
the 1991 collapse of the Soviet Union. (US-Russia-Syria-Arms Sale)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The new Israeli government led by Ehud Barak took
office Tuesday after his coalition was approved by the Knesset (
Parliament) by a large majority.
</P>
<P>
After hours of debate, the Knesset voted 75 to 29, with 11
abstentions, to approve the new government. (Israel-Government)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUSAKA -- Peace talks aimed at ending the 11-month conflict in
Congo (K) fell in deadlock Tuesday after Rwanda said it would not
back down on a demand that exiled Hutu militia be disarmed,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The officials attending the meeting here said that the talks,
which have been dragging on for close to two weeks in Zambian
capital Lusaka, were now on the verge of collapse. (Zambia-Congo
(K) Talks) 
