<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile Worries About Pinochet's Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Chilean Foreign Minister Juan
Gabriel Valdes said Tuesday the Chilean government has information
that shows the health of lifetime Senator Augusto Pinochet is
deteriorating on a daily basis.
</P>
<P>
After studying the results of the latest examinations, Valdes
did not rule out the possibility of requesting the release of
Pinochet on humanitarian grounds, since his health may deteriorate
to a dangerous level.
</P>
<P>
He said that President Eduardo Frei indicated on May 21 that he
would like the senator to return to Chile.
</P>
<P>
The 83-year-old Pinochet was arrested in October in London at
the request of Spanish judge Baltasar Garzon, who wants to try him
for human rights violations against Chilean Spaniards during 1973-
1990 when he was in office as president.
</P>
<P>
President Frei has tried to get Pinochet freed, arguing that
Garzon's request infringes upon Chile's sovereignty, for foreign
courts have no jurisdiction over Chilean ex-leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
