<HEADLINE> Chief of U.S. South Command Visits Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chief of the U.S. South Command,
General Charles E. Wilhelm, visited Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
The general toured the air base at Manta, where he inspected
the works of the center against drugs, an Ecuadorian official said
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Wilhelm also met with Ecuadorian Defense Minister Jose Gallardo
at the air-base Mariscal Sucre.
</P>
<P>
The Unites States still has a control program for the anti-drug
campaign in Ecuador, and uses the Manta base as its operational
headquarters in the country.
</P>
<P>
On July 15, Wilhelm will visit Ecuador again, as the United
States is trying to gain an extension of the agreement which
allows it to use the Manta air-base.
</P>
<P>
The South Command, the U.S. operational force for Latin America,
has its base in Miami. 
</P>
