<HEADLINE> Bulgaria: No Political Obstacle to Russian KFOR Overflight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 6 (Xinhua) - Russian Prime Minister Sergei
Stepashin called his Bulgarian counterpart Ivan Kostov Tuesday on
the matter concerning the agreements reached between Russia and
NATO on the KFOR issue, the Information Service said.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Kostov assured Stepashin that Bulgaria has
no political obstacle to granting Russian KFOR planes air pass
over its territory.
</P>
<P>
Kostov also acquainted Stepashin with the Bulgarian
constitutional and legal provisions concerning the overflight of
foreign aircraft over Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the two leaders discussed Russian companies'
interests in privatization and investment projects in Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
Stepashin repeated his desire to visit Bulgaria with the date
to be specified later. 
