<HEADLINE> China's Top Ten Trade Provinces, Municipalities (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Following are latest facts and
figures about China's top ten trade provinces and municipalities
in the first five months of this year, provided by the General
Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Guangdong Province dropped 4.8 percent
to 48.762 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports decreased 14.7 percent
to 25.867 billion U.S. dollars and imports grew 9.5 percent to 22.
895 billion.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Shanghai increased 19.5 percent to 13.
237 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports and imports went up 18.2
percent and 20.7 percent to 6.674 billion U.S. dollars and 6.562
billion U.S. dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Beijing went up 13.1 percent to 12.836
billion U.S. dollars. Its exports declined 11.2 percent to 3.599
billion U.S. dollars and imports soared 26.6 percent to 9.237
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Jiangsu Province increased 14.4 percent
to 10.934 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports and imports went up 13.
9 percent and 15.2 percent to 6.402 billion U.S. dollars and 4.532
billion U.S. dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Fujian Province dropped 2.2 percent to
6.819 billion U.S. dollars. Its export and import went down 3.3
percent and 0.7 percent to 3.9 billion U.S. dollars and 2.918
billion U.S. dollars respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
