<HEADLINE> China's Top Ten Trade Provinces, Municipalities (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
-- The trade volume of Shandong Province grew 3.8 percent to 6.
749 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports and imports increased 5.6
percent and 1 percent to 4.219 billion U.S. dollars and 2.53
billion respectively.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Zhejiang Province increased 13.7
percent to 6.407 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports and imports
went up 11.5 percent and 18.9 percent to 4.458 billion U.S.
dollars and 1.949 billion respectively.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Tianjin soared 20 percent to 4.856
billion U.S. dollars. Its exports and imports went up 24.1 percent
and 15.6 percent to 2.581 billion U.S. dollars and 2.276 billion
respectively.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Liaoning Province increased 10 percent
to 4.787 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports and imports went up 2.1
percent and 22.2 percent to 2.692 billion U.S. dollars and 2.095
billion respectively.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Sichuan Province soared 79.3 percent to
1.148 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports grew 1.4 percent to 460.
593 million U.S. dollars while import soared 270.3 percent to 687.
021 million U.S. dollars. 
