<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade of Enterprises Involving Overseas Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Following are facts and figures
about trade volume of the enterprises involving overseas capital
in China in the first five months this year, provided by the
General Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of cooperative enterprises went down 20.7
percent to 5.428 billion U.S. dollars, with exports down 15.7
percent to 2.874 billion U.S. dollars and imports down 25.7
percent to 2.553 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of joint ventures grew 2.9 percent to 28.
341 billion U.S. dollars, with exports up 0.6 percent to 13.475
billion U.S. dollars and imports up 5.1 percent to 14.866 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of solely foreign-funded enterprises went
up 14.3 percent to 28.877 billion U.S. dollars, with exports up 15.
5 percent to 15.542 billion U.S. dollars and imports up 13 percent
to 13.335 billion U.S. dollars.  
