<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: China's Major Trade Partners in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Sino-South African trade volume totaled 629.168 million U.S.
dollars, down 0.1 percent from the same period of 1998. Exports
went down 25.4 percent to 266.001 million U.S. dollars while
imports soared 32.9 percent to 363.167 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Sino-Egyptian trade volume totaled 265.587 million U.S.
dollars, up 26.2 percent from that of 1998. Exports rose 25.4
percent to 247.634 million U.S. dollars while imports surged 37.9
percent to 17.953 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- Trade volume with Nigeria was 221.287 million U.S. dollars,
up 33.8 percent from that of 1998. Exports increased 8.4 percent
to 157.767 million U.S. dollars and imports soared 220 percent to
63.52 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
