<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
today's major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin said here yesterday while meeting with
the visiting president of the 53rd Session of the United Nations
General Assembly that the UN can play its due role so long as all
member nations adhere to the aim and principles stipulated in the
UN Charter.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told Didier Opertti, who also serves as Uruguayan foreign
minister, that all member nations' adherence to the UN Charter
will also lead to an effective maintenance of world peace and a
strong development momentum across the world.
</P>
<P>
Opertti arrived here Sunday evening for a seven-day official
visit to China.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Zhu Rongji yesterday urged government functionaries
at all level, especially leading officials, to be fully aware of
strengthening the legal structure of the government and to be
serious about administrating by law.
</P>
<P>
The overall implementation of the policy of "administrating by
law" is an important component for implementing the fundamental
strategy of "governing the country according to law" and an
inevitable requirement for building a clean, hard-working and
highly efficient government.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made these remarks here yesterday at the closing session of
a two day national conference on administrating by law.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin is to pay a state visit to the
State of Mongolia from July 15 to 17 at the invitation of
Mongolian President Nachagyn Bagbandy.
</P>
<P>
-- The International Cultural Exchange Center of China (ICECC)
celebrated the 15th anniversary of its founding yesterday and its
council members held a meeting.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao met with those participating
in the celebration and the conference. He expressed his hope that
the ICECC will make new contributions to the friendly cooperation
between Chinese people and people of the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China yesterday reiterated its strong protest to the
government of Papua New Guinea (PNG) after it signed a communique
establishing so-called "diplomatic ties" with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
China also "firmly opposed" attempts by some United States
congressmen to strengthen "U.S.-Taiwan relations" and to further
interfere in China's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
-- The Communist Party of China (CPC) is going to remodel its
central departments in a bid to enhance the efficiency of their
work as well as to strengthen and improve the leadership of the
Party.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, at
yesterday's work conference focused on the move.
</P>
<P>
Hu explained that this major reform program closely follows the
restructuring of the State Council and the current reform of local
governments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
