<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Trade of China's Coastal Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Following are facts and figures
about trade volumes of China's coastal cities in January-May
period of 1999, provided by the General Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
-- Shanghai's trade volume reached 13.237 billion U.S. dollars,
up 19.5 percent. Its exports grew 18.2 percent to 6.674 billion U.
S. dollars while imports went up 20.7 percent to 6.562 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Guangzhou increased 2.4 percent to 5.
149 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports declined 17 percent to 2.56
billion U.S. dollars while imports soared 33.1 percent to 2.589
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Tianjin went up 20 percent to 4.856
billion U.S. dollars. Its exports increased 24.1 percent to 2.581
billion U.S. dollars while imports grew 15.6 percent to 2.276
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Qingdao, Shandong province, increased
12.1 percent to 3.153 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports went up 6.
5 percent to 1.972 billion U.S. dollars while imports reached 1.
181 billion U.S. dollars, up 22.8 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
