<HEADLINE> Cuba, Argentina Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Cuba and
Argentina signed Tuesday a cooperation agreement, which
constitutes a sequel to an earlier successful agreement.
</P>
<P>
Cuban Minister for Foreign Investment and Economic Cooperation
Ibrahim Ferradaz and Argentine ambassador to Cuba Luis Santos
Casale signed the document which contains 55 projects in a
spectrum of fields including agriculture, industry, higher
education, the environment and public administration.
</P>
<P>
The projects for the 1999-2000 period are to be evaluated by
the Argentine Fund for Horizontal Cooperation which aims to
promote the transfer of knowledge and experience of Argentine
technicians and scientists.
</P>
<P>
Last January, both countries struck their first protocol of
similar cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
