<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Hopes to Further Develop Relations With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan treasures its close
relations with China and sees great potential in developing them
in the next century, Kazakh Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign
Minister Kasymzhomart Kemelevich Tokayev said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a written reply to questions by Xinhua correspondents,
Tokayev said he is scheduled to visit China on July 7-15 to
discuss with Chinese leaders ways to strengthen bilateral
cooperation in the short and long run, especially in the economic
and trade area, and to exchange views on regional and
international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
He said his tour is in preparation of the autumn visit to China
by Kazakh President Nursultan Abishevich Nazarbayev, expressing
confidence that the president's visit is sure to give a new
impetus to the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Tokayev recalled frequent high-level meetings between the two
countries in the past few years as well as their active contacts
in various fields, which have strongly promoted bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China is Kazakhstan's biggest trading partner in
Asia with an annual trade volume of 500 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister praised Sino-Kazakh cooperation in
maintaining regional security, saying that the summit mechanism
between China, Kazakhstan, Russia, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan plays
an important role in maintaining the security and stability of
Asia and even the world.
</P>
<P>
The five countries signed an agreement on strengthening
military confidence in border areas in 1996 and another one on
reducing military forces in border areas in 1997. These documents,
Tokayev said, "are unprecedented" in international relations.
</P>
<P>
He said the agreement between Kazakhstan and China on their
border line has solved the most complicated problems in their
relations and set an example for other countries of resolving
border disputes in a civilized manner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
