<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Acting Defense Minister Escapes Rebel Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's acting Defense Minister
General Anurudha Ratwatte Tuesday escaped a Tamil rebel attack
while on an inspection tour of the front in the north of the
country, said reports reaching here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The rebels fired a barrage of artillery in the direction of the
camp at Welioya, about 250 kilometers north of the capital of
Colombo, while the minister and others were there but all escaped
unhurt, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
The army took immediate steps to bolster the security following
the attack. The minister went ahead and completed his tour of
inspection.
</P>
<P>
This was the second time the rebels had made an attempt on the
minister's life. The first was in December 1998 under similar
circumstances at Oddusuddan in northern Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been waging a separatist war against the
government since 1983 for a homeland for minority Tamils in Sri
Lanka's north and east. 
</P>
