<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Opens Securities Supervision Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south China
's Guangdong Province, recently opened a securities supervision
office, one of the nine branches operated by the China Securities
Regulatory Commission.
</P>
<P>
Establishment of the office was part of a nationwide effort to
reduce risk on the securities market, reform and improve the
supervision system for securities and futures transactions, ensure
a healthy and stable market, and promote continuing economic
development.
</P>
<P>
The office will regulate and supervise activities on the
securities exchange and related business activities carried out by
law firms, accounting firms and evaluation agencies.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou office will also have the right to render
punishment for illegal securities transactions and will arbitrate
cases involving business disputes. 
