<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents on Rise in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Traffic accidents continue to
increase at an alarming rate in Vietnam, Vietnam's English daily
Vietnam News reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statistics released by the National Traffic Safety
Commission (NTSC) show 19,975 traffic accidents occurred
throughout the country in 1998, resulting in 6,067 deaths and over
22,700 injuries. In the first five months of this year, 2,883
people were killed and 10,999 injured in 9,656 road accidents
across the country.
</P>
<P>
The NTSC blames over-speeding for 33 percent of these cases,
violations of traffic rules and regulations for 38 percent,
driving under the influence of alcohol for 8.5 percent, and other
reasons including old vehicles and equipment, for the remaining
20-odd percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
