<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ferreira Advances, Stoltenberg Ousted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Wayne Ferreira of
South Africa moved into next round while second-seeded Jason
Stoltenberg of Australia was upset at the Hall of Fame Tennis
Championships in Rhode Island, United States, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ferreira, a former top-10 player now ranked 32nd, romped
Italian Mose Navarra 6-3, 6-3 with his serves and volleys.
</P>
<P>
Stoltenberg, an Australian who lost in the semi-finals last
year as the No.1 seed, conceded a three-set match loss to American
Jonathan Stark.
</P>
<P>
After splitting the first two sets, Stark jumped out to a 3-0
lead in the third before nearly giving away the match with a
double fault on a break point. After slamming his racquet in
frustration, Stark persevered and took the match 6-4, 3-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Eighth-seed Sebastien Lareau was the only other seeded player
to fall, losing to Kenneth Carlsen 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Other winners included third seed David Prinosil, seventh seed
Daniel Nestor and unseeded Wayne Arthurs, Christian Vinck and
Chris Woodruff.
</P>
<P>
In the doubles action, India's Leander Paes, the world's top
doubles player, teamed with Arthurs to beat Tuomas Ketola and
Rogier Wassen 6-2, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
