<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hke070716 -Thai Industries Well Below Production Capacity: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's industries are still
operating far below their production capacities despite optimism
shared by government agencies that the country's economy has been
on the right track of recovery, an industry ministry survey
available here Wednesday said.
</P>
<P>
Some 13 major manufacturing industries will use only about 30
to 50 percent of their total production capacity in 1999, which is
about the same as last year, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
To break even or reach economies of scale in production, one
has to use up to 70 to 80 percent of available capacity.
</P>
<P>
Producers of steel, cement and glass in the construction sector
reportedly now use only 40 percent of their available capacity, of
which 30 percent is consumed domestically while the remaining 10
percent is exported.
</P>
<P>
Shifting more of their focus to export markets, producers of
electrical appliances manage to use about 45 to 60 percent of
their capacity, a level which barely allows them to survive.
</P>
<P>
Most heavily affected are producers of automobiles and
motorcycles as they use only 9.5 percent and 24 percent of their
capacities respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, producers of all types of dairy products manage to use
65 percent of their capacity while producers of plastic and paper
products reportedly use 75 to 85 percent as their products are in
high demand by exporters for their packaging.
</P>
<P>
The main reason why producers are not using their full capacity
this year is that exported products do not fetch good prices and
competitors in the international markets have lower production
costs, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
Very few producers is expected to make profits this year and
additional investments will be curtailed for years to come, the
survey said.
</P>
<P>
Production in the industrial sector accounts for about half of
the country's gross domestic product. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990707.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
