<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Opposition to Stage Nationwide Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's opposition alliance will
stage a dawn-to-dusk hartal (strike) across the country on
Thursday in protest against the passage in parliament of what they
said an "anti-people" budget, soaring prices of essentials and
deteriorating law and order situation.
</P>
<P>
This will be the seventh nationwide shutdown sponsored by the
opposition alliance this year.
</P>
<P>
Opposition Leader Khaleda Zia said on Tuesday that the shutdown
was aimed at delivering the people from sufferings and
safeguarding the country's independence and sovereignty through
compelling the government to resign, handing over power to a
caretaker government, The Bangladesh Observer newspaper reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The opposition alliance, comprising the Bangladesh Nationalist
Party, the Jatiya Party, the Jamaat-e-Islami and the Islami Oikya
Jote, would enforce the strike to protest the "anti-people"
budget, "conspiracy" for gas export, providing corridor (to
India), she said.
</P>
<P>
The Central Liaison Committee of the four-party alliance,
meanwhile, has also announced a fresh program to gear up the
anti-government movement.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, the four parties will observe separate
demonstrations across the country under their respective party
banner on July 16, and stage road marches from the capital city
Dhaka to different parts of the country between July 25 and 27.
</P>
<P>
Hartal is a common political phenomenon in Bangladesh, where
opposition parties call hartals to oppose the ruling party while
the latter adopts anti-hartal activities, often resulting in
clashes and causing heavy economic losses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
