<HEADLINE> Chinese Chemical Plant Increases Organic Silicon Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Xinghuo Chemical Plant in east
China's Jiangxi Province recently completed trials of a
domestically designed and manufactured processing facility with an
annual production capacity of 20,000 tons of organic silicon.
</P>
<P>
The breakthrough will substantially increase China's production
of organic silicon, a high-tech chemical material widely used in
the national defense, space and aviation, electronic,
petrochemical, pharmaceutical, textile and construction sectors.
</P>
<P>
The list of only a few countries capable of producing the high-
tech product includes the United States, Japan, France and Germany.
The new facility will eliminate China's heavy reliance on imported
organic silicon products.
</P>
<P>
Xinghuo Chemical Plant is a subsidiary of China National Blue
Star Chemical Cleaning Co. which is headquartered in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The plant produced close to 10,000 tons of organic silicon in
1997 and introduced a technological upgrade project in the latter
part of 1998 to develop the new 20,000-ton facility.
</P>
<P>
Blue Star plans to establish a organic silicon group and four
production bases across the country in a bid to increase China's
annual organic silicon output to over 100,000 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
