<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top-seeded Hrbaty Upset in Swedish Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 6 (Xinhua)-- American Jeff Tarango breezed over
top-seeded Dominik Hrbaty of Slovakia 6-1, 6-2 on Tuesday in the
opening round of the 325,000 U.S. dollars Swedish Open tennis
tournament in Bastad, Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Thomas Johansson of Sweden beat Spain's Alberto
Berasategui, runner-up in the 1994 French Open, in a hard-fought
three-set match 6-3, 1-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Spain's German Puentes eliminated eighth seed Jan Kroslak of
Slovakia 4-6, 6-1, 6-3; wild-card entry Nicklas Kulti of Sweden
outscored Michael Kohlmann of Germany 1-6, 6-4, 6-3; and qualifier
Markus Hipfl of Austria upset seventh-seeded Gaston Gaudio of
Argentina 6-3, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
In other actiona, Hernan Gumy of Argentina eliminated Italian
Davide Sanguinetti 6-2, 6-1, and Norway's Christian Ruud, sixth
seed, defeated Swedish qualifier Johan Ortegren 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Four-time singles winner Magnus Gustafsson and fellow Swede
Magnus Norman advanced to the doubles second round with identical
6-2, 6-4 victories over Andrew Painter of Australia and Byron
Talbot of South Africa. 
</P>
