<HEADLINE> Turkish Minister Attempts Suicide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkish State Minister in charge of
the treasury Hikmet Ulugbay suffered minor injuries after a
suicide attempt Wednesday at his home in Ankara.
</P>
<P>
Local Hurriyet (Freedom) reported that the 60-year-old Ulugbay
fired at his own jaw bone, at his home in Umit Koy, outskirts of
Ankara, at 00:45 local time (21:45 GMT Tuesday).
</P>
<P>
His wife and son heard the shot and rushed to him. They
prevented him from firing more shots and called the police.
</P>
<P>
After the emergency operation in the hospital, Ulugbay's life
is not in danger now.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Ulugbay had leaked official documents to a
brokerage firm owned by a cousin of Mesut Yilmaz, chairman of the
Motherland Party and a coalition partner. The firms was accused of
using the information to manipulate stock.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz claimed Tuesday that he was shown the document by
Ulugbay himself. 
