<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The tourism authorities in north
China's Shanxi province is straightening out its tourism sector by
penalizing those travel agencies that have violated industry
regulations.
</P>
<P>
A total of two international travel agencies and 15 domestic
ones have received warnings for their illegal activities or poor
management, while four other domestic ones have had their business
licenses revoked.
</P>
<P>
"The move is designed to overhaul the tourism sector and
encourage fair competition, so as to guide the Shanxi's tourism
business into a sound development track," said a provincial
tourism official.
</P>
<P>
Located at the middle reaches of the Yellow River, Shanxi is a
cradle of the Chinese civilization, and known for its treasury of
traditional Chinese buildings and natural beauty.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, Shanxi achieved a tourism income of 5.6 billion yuan,
up 20.97 percent from the previous year.  
