<HEADLINE> Papua New Guinea's Prime Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Papua New Guinea's Prime Minister
Bill Skate announced Wednesday that he had resigned, the
Australian Associated Press (AAP) reported.
</P>
<P>
Skate told reporters that his resignation was intended to
restore political stability to Papua New Guinea (PNG), and he
would hand in his resignation to PNG Governor-General Sir Silas
Atopare Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Skate had received legal advice that he would remain acting
prime minister until a new prime minister could be chosen by
parliament on July 13, according to AAP.
</P>
<P>
It was unclear who would succeed Skate as prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Skate's coalition partner the People's Democratic Movement
recently deserted the government to join the opposition.
</P>
<P>
Mekere Morauta, leader of the People's Democratic Party, would
appear to have the largest block of support in parliament but
Wednesday's resignation may completely change the political
dynamics in PNG. 
</P>
