<HEADLINE> North China Port City Launches Medical Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin branch of the Bank of
Communications has led Chinese banks in launching a new loan
service to finance families in urgent need of loans for medical
treatment of their members.
</P>
<P>
Xu Shouye became the first to receive such loans in China, when
he borrowed 18,000 yuan from the bank to treat his son's
leucocythemia. Before that, Xu had used up all his personal
savings as well as money donated by and borrowed from his
colleagues, which ran up to nearly 200,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
People may mortgage treasury bonds, depository notes, financial
bonds and corporate bonds to the bank for loans up to 100,000 yuan,
which will mature in one or two years.
</P>
<P>
"This new loan is designed as an item of the individual
consumption credits, and we start the loan service to help
families with financial difficulties as a result of the severe
disease of the family members," said Zhang Xiping, a deputy
manager from the Bank of Communications' Tianjin branch.  
</P>
