<HEADLINE> DRC Refugees Pouring into Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has received more
than 22,500 refugees from the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC)
since rebels in the central African country took up arms against
government forces last August.
</P>
<P>
Statistics provided by the Ministry of Home Affairs indicate
that a record of 2,167 DRC refugees flowed into west Tanzania's
Kigoma Region on June 29 alone, Daily News reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Some of the refugees in Kigoma told the newspaper that they had
fled renewed fightings between rebels and pro-government Maimai
militia in rebel- held areas of Kivu Province in the east of DRC.
</P>
<P>
The new arrivals since last August have brought the total
number of DRC refugees in Tanzania to 86,700 by June 30, according
to a report by the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees
(UNHCR). 
</P>
</TEXT>
