<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandan Coffee Export Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's coffee exports have
maintained steady recovery with 28.66 million U.S. dollars in
export revenue in June, up from 19.36 million dollars in May,
representing a 48.1 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
The latest export figures issued by Uganda Coffee Development
Authority indicated that the volume of coffee exported also rose
by 56.3 percent, The Monitor newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Coffee exports during the first three quarters of the coffee
year 1998/ 1999 (October 1998-June 1999) increased by 34.7 percent
in volume and 15.1 percent in value, compared with the same period
of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The Coffee Development Authority attributed the improvement in
performance in June to full activity from the main coffee season
in Uganda' s southern and western regions. It was also enhanced by
the relatively stable financial sector which facilitated
mobilization of fund, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
