<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The latest census on French population shows that happiness
and good quality of life are two key elements for attracting
people to settle in a place to live. Not only geography, but also
the efforts by local governments to improve living quality and
environment are important to draw people. Geographical closeness
to the sea is no longer sufficient to make people come to live.
</P>
<P>
-- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak kept a prudent tone when
he made his swearing in speech at the Knesset on Tuesday,
promising to make peace with the Palestinians, Syria and Lebanon
as soon as possible. Although he did not make precise his peace
plan, his offer was welcome by Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
and Syrian President Hafez Assad.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- In his speech to the Israeli parliament the Knesset, Prime
Minister Ehud Barak expressed his will to implement a policy of ``
courageous peace'' with Arabs. He promised to implement the Wye
Plantation Agreement with the Palestinians, and to relaunch peace
talks with Syria to attain a peace agreement on the basis of U.N.
Security Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
-- More and more French companies are adopting the system of
share holding by their employees, which is increasing the
purchasing power of shareholders and changing social relations
within the enterprises. Big enterprises like Saint-Gobain, Renault,
France Telecom, Air France and Credit Lyonnais have launched big
operations aimed at letting employees share the results of
business. 
</P>
