<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Emir Re-Names Crown Prince as Prime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Emir Jaber Al-Ahmed
Al-Sabah on Wednesday re-named Crown Prince Sheikh Saad
Al-Abdullah Al-Sabah as Prime Minister and asked him to form a new
government.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti Emir made the appointment three days after he
accepted the resignation of Saad and his government, the Kuwait
News Agency reported
</P>
<P>
The former government resigned under the Constitution on July
4, when final results of the country's National Assembly
(parliament) elections were officially announced.
</P>
<P>
The Emir has asked the resigned cabinet to act as a caretaker
government until a new cabinet is formed within two weeks. 
