<HEADLINE> Cabinet Reshuffle Nearly Completed: Thai PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The weeks-long drama of party power
struggle pending a cabinet reshuffle is expected to end shortly as
all coalition members except the Chart Pattana Party (CPP) have
already handed in their lists of proposal, Thai Prime Minister
Chuan Leekpai said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
As for CPP's quota in the government, Chuan said the Democrat
Party and CPP have reached agreement so that the reshuffle can be
completed within this week.
</P>
<P>
The reshuffle will not affect the government's administrative
operation of the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sanan Kachornprasart, secretary-general of the
Democrat, said he expected the list from CPP Thursday.
</P>
<P>
CPP leader Korn Dabbaransi denied that there is dispute within
the party over cabinet seats, saying the party is selecting
suitable candidates.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that CPP had asked for the seat of first
minister in science portfolio and a deputy in the interior
portfolio, but was rejected by the Democrat.
</P>
<P>
Latest reports said it is very likely that CPP will be
allocated with a deputy in the transport ministry and a minister
in the prime minister's office.
</P>
<P>
The current government coalition, grouping six parties, enjoys
a 234-seat majority in the 283-strong House of Representatives.
</P>
</TEXT>
