<HEADLINE> SADC Urged to Reduce Reliance on Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano has highlighted the challenge facing the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) as how to reduce to the lowest level
its reliance on the outside world.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement to Mozambican reporters Tuesday in
Durban, South Africa, where he was attending the Southern Africa
Economic Summit.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the cooperation between SADC members, without
excluding cooperation with the outside world.!!
</P>
<P>
Another challenge, he said, is the lack of professionals in
most SADC countries. Moreover, the SADC should also enhance
cooperation in eliminating AIDS, malaria and other diseases.
</P>
<P>
A strict administrative mechanism on armed conflicts is another
issue of common concern.
</P>
<P>
"We are faced with a challenge of integration to resolve
unsettled issues," said Chissano who is deputy president of the
SADC.
</P>
<P>
Chissano referred to the Southern Africa Economic Summit in
Durban as " successful", saying the region is of much importance
to Africa, Europe and other regions of the world. 
</P>
