<HEADLINE> EU Delegation Visits Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A European Union (EU) delegation is
currently paying a three-day visit here.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, which arrived here Tuesday, is scheduled to
meet leaders of both the government and the opposition National
League for Democracy (NLD) later Wednesday, according to sources
at the British Embassy here.
</P>
<P>
The EU delegation, on its first ever trip to Yangon since the
ruling military government came to power in late 1988, will make
consultations with the government on matters related to the
opposition party, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The NLD won the general election in May 1990, sponsored by the
government. However, as there have been wide differences between
the government and the winning party over the drawing-up of a new
state constitution, the handing over of power remains unrealized
up to now.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, an envoy of the U.N. secretary-general, Alvaro de
Soto, himself an assistant U.N. secretary-general, visited Myanmar
in October 1998 and met with both government and NLD leaders for
the same consultations. 
</P>
