percent, while Utilities, Properties and Commerce &AMP; Industry all
suffered losses of 2.80 percent, 0.57 percent and 0.48 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares closed lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 4.43 percent while the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corporations Index fell 2.86 percent.
</P>
<P>
The share prices opened lower Wednesday morning with the Hang
Seng Index standing at 14,326.06 points, shortly after the opening.
The prices then rebounded by 0.16 percent, or 22.29 points, to
close the morning session at 14,394.90. 
