<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 2 Injured in Philippines' Gas Tank Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A truck carrying 800 cooking gas
tanks overturned and exploded after it sideswiped a car in
Pangasinan province in the northern Philippines, killing at least
one and injuring two others shortly before dawn Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Police report received here said a delivery man of the truck
was burned to death while trying to run away from the exploding
cargo of the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the truck was speeding towards north
when it tried to avoid an approaching car. The driver of the car
and his companion suffered minor injuries and slight burns.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the truck and his two other helpers survived the
tragedy after they managed to run away when their vehicle rammed
into the elevated pavement of a bridge and turned upside down.
</P>
<P>
All 800 units of cooking gas tanks exploded from the time the
accident happened at about 11:45 p.m. Tuesday and the fire lasted
until around 1:00 a.m. Wednesday, said the report. 
</P>
