<HEADLINE> Pak Expels Indian Official on Spying Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government on
Wednesday expelled Yog Raj Vij, an official of the Indian High
Commission here, on spying charges.
</P>
<P>
A press release by the Foreign Office said the Pakistani
government has declared Yog Raj Vij as persona-non-grata, for he
has been found "indulging in activities incompatible with his
official status."
</P>
<P>
The Indian official has been told to leave Pakistan within a
week.
</P>
<P>
Indian Deputy High Commissioner Ruchi Gansham was summoned to
the Foreign Office Wednesday and was informed of the decision.
</P>
<P>
The Indian High Commission has alleged that Yog Raj Vij was
kidnapped and severely beaten by a group of 10 to 12 people from
Pakistan's Intelligence Agency Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani side, however, said an investigation into the
Indian allegation is under way.
</P>
<P>
India expelled a Pakistani High Commission official in New
Delhi last month, also on the spying charges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
