</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990707.0269 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Legislature Condemns U.S. Anti-China Moves (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taiwan is part of China's territory and the Taiwan issue is
purely China's internal affair. Both of the aforementioned facts
are widely recognized by the international community, including
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The perverse moves of some U.S. legislators constitute a grave
provocation to Chinese sovereignty and gross interference in China
's internal affairs. The Foreign Affairs Committee members
strongly condemn and reject the actions.
</P>
<P>
Since China and the United States forged diplomatic ties, the
ups and downs in their relations have centered mainly on the issue
of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
A point well worth noting is that the principles set forth in
the three Sino-U.S. joint communiques have provided the political
foundation for the development of bilateral relations. The U.S.
Congress and government are obligated to strictly adhere to the
principles and faithfully carry out their promise to support the "
one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Practice proves that whenever these principles are observed,
Sino-U.S. relations grow smoothly, and that whenever these
principles are infringed upon, Sino-U.S. relations witness twists
and turns, or stagnation, or even retrogression.
</P>
<P>
Any damage to bilateral relations runs counter to the
fundamental interests and aspirations of the people in both
nations.
</P>
<P>
The NPC strongly demands that the U.S. Congress take Sino-U.S.
relations into full account, abide by the principles enshrined in
the three joint communiques and take steps to stop the
aforementioned conspiracy that will damage bilateral relations,
and prevent further deterioration in Sino-U.S. relations which
have already encountered many trials and hardships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990707.0270 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 12:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Security Officials Warn Against Terrorist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 7 (Xinhua) -- As Prime Minister Ehud Barak
launched peace initiatives with Arab countries, Israeli security
officials Wednesday warned against terrorist attacks by extremist
Islamic groups.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio quoted the security officials as saying that the
extremist Islamic groups, which oppose peace with Israel, may step
up their activities after the new Israeli government took office
Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The officials said militant groups, such as Hamas and Islamic
Jihad, may carry out terrorist attacks, including kidnapping
Israeli soldiers or civilians, in the near future.
</P>
<P>
They said that Israeli General Security Service and other
security institutions have prepared for the possible attacks.
</P>
<P>
They added that Israel has asked for further cooperation of the
security forces of Palestinian National Authority (PNA) in a bid
to prevent the attacks.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement of Barak's office, the prime minister
is due to meet Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and PNA Chairman
Yasser Arafat within days as an effort to push forward the Middle
East peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The militants belonged to Hamas and Islamic Jihad are against
the peace talks with Israel and have been behind a series of
attacks, including suicide bombings, aimed at scuttling the
peace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
