<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Medicine Technology Transferred to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Indian National Research and
Development Corporation (NRDC) announced here Wednesday that it
has transferred to the United States a technology for preparing
drugs for heart diseases and diabetes.
</P>
<P>
The technology was transferred to the San Diego-based Diakron
Pharmaceutical Inc. which was expected to use the technology to
manufacture certain bioactive compounds -- which help lower
cholesterol and glucose levels in blood -- from natural products
like garlic, fenugreek and banyan bark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
