<HEADLINE> IBM's Chinese Home Page To Deal With The Y2K Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The U.S.'s IBM, one of the world's
biggest computer makers, has opened a Chinese home page to help
Chinese solve their Y2K problems.
</P>
<P>
People can find a wide range of choices there, like the IBM
users Guide: Challenging Y2K, solving Y2K in IBM products, and
emergency solutions on the company's web site: http:// www.ibm.com.
cn.
</P>
<P>
The Y2K or millennium bug problem refers to troubles expected
to be caused by the fact that computers only recognize the last
two digits in their year recognition programs and therefore will
be wrong about the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
An IBM China Corporation executive says that the Chinese home
page is a part of the firm's world-wide efforts to solve the Y2K
problem.  
</P>
