<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Preparations are underway for the
22nd Congress of the Universal Postal Union (UPU), which will take
place from August 23 to September 15 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
By July 5, 1,748 representatives and staff members from 146 UPU
member countries and 25 international institutions had registered
for the congress.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo, who is chairman of the China
Organizing Committee for the congress, said at a meeting yesterday
that the Chinese government is paying a great deal of attention to
the congress and he asked departments concerned to try their best
to see to it that the congress is a success.
</P>
<P>
The congress is one of the highest level international meetings
to be held in China at the turn of the century. It is the first
plenary meeting of a United Nations special organization to be
held in China and the first UPU congress that China will host.
