<HEADLINE> Chinese Building Materials Becoming More Profitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua)-- China's building materials industry
had sales of 87 billion yuan (10 billion US dollars) in the first
5 months of this year, up 14.4 percent from the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The industry cut its losses by nearly 2 billion yuan. Its net
losses were 570 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The improved profitability comes from the government's
increased spending on infrastructure since last year and the
building materials industry saw its output value and sales grow
more than 10 percentage points on an annual basis.
</P>
