<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Foreign Currency Assets Decrease in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary Authority
(HKMA) announced here Wednesday that the official foreign currency
assets of Hong Kong amounted to 88.6 billion U.S. dollars at the
end of June 1999.
</P>
<P>
The figure represents a 300-million-U.S. dollar drop from the
previous month.
</P>
<P>
In terms of foreign currency reserves ranking, Hong Kong is the
world's fifth largest holders of foreign currency reserves after
Japan, China's mainland, Taiwan and Germany.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign currency assets of 88.6 billion U.S. dollars
represent over seven times the currency in circulation or about 37
percent of Hong Kong dollar M3, one of the highest ratios in the
world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
