<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Banks Launch Mobile Banking Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Customers of the Hongkong and
Shanghai Banking Corporation (HSBC) and Hang Seng Bank can conduct
their financial transactions by their mobile phones from September
thanks to the mobile banking services to be launched by these two
banks.
</P>
<P>
The services allow customers to check their HK dollar account
balances, transfer funds between their HK dollar accounts and
those of third parties and trade securities by their mobile phones.
</P>
<P>
HSBC and Hang Seng Bank are the first banks in Hong Kong to
offer their customers securities trading by mobile phone.
</P>
<P>
Using these new services, customers will be able to
conveniently conduct their day-to-day banking business and buy and
sell shares.
</P>
<P>
The screen-based service available through mobile banking makes
it easy for customers to check and confirm their transactions.
</P>
<P>
Those customers who subscribe to roaming services will be able
to check on their balances and do their personal banking even when
they are traveling outside Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng Bank's Retail Banking General Manager Mok Wai-kin
said that in the future, the mobile banking services will be
developed to include more banking services which will be available
to more customers at both banks.
</P>
<P>
The service has adopted the Triple Data Encryption Standard, an
industry security standard, to avoid unauthorized access to the
content of transaction requests which contain personal information.
Furthermore, access to the service is protected by up to three
levels of PIN protection to safeguard against unauthorized use.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
