<HEADLINE> Gunman Dies In Gun Battle With Police In Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The Public Security Bureau of
Beijing announced today that police shot and killed a gunman in
the Chinese capital last Saturday when he and 3 accomplices were
trying to escape from a bungled robbery.
</P>
<P>
A police bureau spokesman said that the four had attempted to
rob a car in a northern part of the downtown just nearly 2:00 in
the afternoon, and when they failed in the attempt they fled in a
car.
</P>
<P>
When police intercepted them in a western part of the downtown
they fled from the car, running in different directions.
</P>
<P>
Police fired warning shots, then shot one of them who took out
a handgun, killing him in the process. One was injured in the
fight with police and, with another suspect, was apprehended on
the spot. The fourth is still at large.
</P>
<P>
Police later found a hunting rifle in the car.  
</P>
