<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- South Africa should consider a
 tie with the Indian Ocean Rim (IOR) instead of the Southern
African Development Community (SADC), the opposition Democratic
Party said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's engagement with its southern African neighbors
was "faltering and inconsequential". An alliance with the IOR
would enable a more solid and equal engagement with other world
trade blocks, Democracy Party spokesman Nigel Bruce said.
</P>
<P>
Of South Africa's total trade, 35 percent was with Europe, and
that figure was growing, while only seven percent was with SADC
countries and two percent with the rest of Africa.
</P>
<P>
South Africa should seek other trade partners whose economies
were moving in the same direction as its own, suggested Bruce.
