<HEADLINE> China's People's Insurance Group Closes For Good </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- The People's Insurance (Group) Co.
of China (PICC Group) today declared its formal closure, which has
been approved by the State Council, China's cabinet.
</P>
<P>
PICC Group was formed from the People's Insurance Co. of China
(PICC) on August 21, 1996, with 3 subsidiaries: PICC Property,
PICC Life, and PICC Reinsurance.
</P>
<P>
The 3 subsidiaries are being renamed the People's Insurance Co.
of China (PICC), China Life Insurance Co.(CLIC), and China
Reinsurance Co.(CRC).
</P>
<P>
CRC will handle credit and liabilities left by the original
PICC and PICC Reinsurance.
</P>
<P>
PICC Group will transfer its overseas assets to China Insurance
Co. Ltd., and relevant matters of the transfer will be handled by
the China Hongkong (Holdings) Insurance Co. Ltd. on behalf of PICC
Group.
</P>
