<HEADLINE> Macao Lifts Ban on Selling European Dairy Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Retailers in Macao have resumed
selling the dairy products made in Germany, France and the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The Health Department of the Macao government announced the
decision on lifting the ban on sales a few days ago as the
suspected dairy products had been proved blameless.
</P>
<P>
Local retailers said that the sales of dairy products from the
three European countries would not recover in a short period of
time as consumers have turned to the brands from other countries.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with a decision announced by the Health
Department on June 8, trading agents in Macao had been required to
suspend the import and sale of dairy products from the three
European countries. 
</P>
