<HEADLINE> Two Comrades Marathon Medallists Test Positive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Two Comrades Marathon gold
medallists have failed the doping tests and faced the confiscation
of prize money and medals, said Athletics South Africa (ASA) here
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Russian runner-up Viktor Zhdanov tested positive for the
stimulant Ephedrine and four-times gold medallist Mohloli Mahlala
of South Africa tested positive for the banned steroid 19
Norandrosterone, a metabolite of Nandrolone, said ASA.
</P>
<P>
Both could lose the prize money and gold medals they won for
being among the first 10 runners home in the gruelling 89.9-
kilometre (56-mile) run on June 16.
</P>
<P>
Zhdanov finished second to Poland's Jaroslaw Janicki and
Mahlala was sixth in the Comrades, one of the world's greatest
ultra-distance road races.
</P>
<P>
Mahlala has been called to offer an explanation and the IAAF,
the athletics world's governing body, will advise the Russian
athletics federation of the result, ASA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
