<HEADLINE> CPPCC Leader In Favor Of Charitable Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 7 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese leader has advocated
charitable activities, saying that "helping the needy and
conducting charitable activities" should become a trend in China.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, the Chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made the remarks during a visit
to Heilongjiang Province July 2-7, where he said that displaying
the traditional morals of the Chinese people, promoting socialist
ethical and cultural progress, and continuing the government
policy to allow part of the people to become well-off first and to
achieve common riches at the end is very important.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a standing committee member of the political bureau of
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, visited new houses
of some villagers who were made homeless by last year's summer
floods that devastated this northeastern province which damaged
820,000 houses and left 900,000 people homeless. A large amount of
donations came in from CPPCC members, private businesspeople, and
from overseas heeding a call by the CPPCC leader.
</P>
<P>
Li urged local government officials to pay greater attention to
the difficulties of some low-income people and to try to guarantee
a daily living for them and warned that this matter should never
be neglected.
</P>
<P>
He called for special care for elderly workers and officials
who have made remarkable contributions to the country and said
that those who have made a fortune earlier than the majority
should help the poor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
