<DOCNO> XIE19990707.0351 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Maps Providing Evidence Of Japanese Invasion Of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Six-two years ago on this day,
Japan started its war of aggression against China by attacking
Beijing across the Lugou Bridge in the southwestern suburbs.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-six military maps related to the incident were made
public today in Liaoning Province. Copies of the maps were
presented by an elderly collector who said he hopes this evidence
can make people more aware of the humiliating past.
</P>
<P>
Three of the maps are marked "Top Secret" and "Burn after Read",
while the rest all bear the word "Military Secret". Seals at the
back of each are for the "Japanese Land Force Officer Training
School".
</P>
<P>
The maps are drawn at a 500,000:1 scale and at the top right
bear the word "Manchuria", the Japanese designation for
northeastern China.
</P>
<P>
Two historians, Professor Xing Anchen from Liaoning University
and Professor Zhang Yipo from Liaoning Provincial Party School,
examined the original maps at the collector's home yesterday and
confirmed their authenticity. They were drawn in such explicit
detail that small paths through each village, and wells, temples
and rivers can be clearly seen.
</P>
<P>
The anonymous collector told the scholars that he bought them
from an old man in Hebei Province 15 years ago who introduced
himself as a former deputy regimental commander of the Kuomintang
(Nationalist Party) Army. The seller said that he got the maps
from an encounter with a small group of Japanese soldiers in Hebei
during the Japanese Aggression War (1937-1945).
</P>
<P>
The scholars said that the maps were made in 1932 and corrected
in 1936. They point out that the maps also substantiate the fact
that the war broke out on July 7 at Lugou Bridge and that this was
a long-premeditated act of aggression. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990707.0352 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 62nd Anniversary Of Outbreak Of Anti-Japanese War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- People in Beijing have gathered
over the past few days to mark the outbreak of the war against
Japanese aggression (1937-1945), an important part of the global
Anti-Fascist War.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin did the calligraphy today for the name of
a 15-m. monument for the Anti-Japanese War that is being built at
Lugou Bridge in the Beijing suburbs, where an incident on July 7,
1937 started the war.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 people visited the Memorial Hall for the War of
Resistance Against Japanese Aggression at Lugou Bridge today, a
larger number than is usually found on weekdays.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition describing how Taiwan compatriots fought against
Japanese invaders was also held at the memorial hall on Tuesday
and there was a symposium on the Lugou Bridge Incident afterwards.
</P>
