<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin expressed hope today that his
forthcoming State visit to Mongolia will add substantial contents
to solid good-neighborly, friendly and cooperative relations
between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during a meeting with a Mongolian press
delegation led by Terbishiin Chimeddorj.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also met this morning with China's Ambassador to the
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia Pan Zhanlin and 3 other embassy
staff members.
</P>
<P>
Chinese, Thai relations emphasized
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, the chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee, met here today with Mongkon Ampornpisit,
the supreme commander of the Armed Forces of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Li spoke about his visit to Thailand in April and emphasized
the traditional friendship between China and Thailand, saying that
exchanges between the governments and parliaments of the two
countries are quite frequent and that the armed forces also have a
long-term and cooperative relationship.
</P>
<P>
Top Legislature Condemns U.S. Anti-China Moves
</P>
<P>
The Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) today expressed
its strong condemnation and opposition to recent U.S. anti-China
actions concerning the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of the NPC Foreign Affairs Committee made
the remarks when commenting on anti-China amendments to the U.S.
National Defense Appropriations Act and on the Taiwan Security
Enhancement Act proposed by the U.S. Congress.
</P>
<P>
