<HEADLINE> Chinese Ambassador: World Peace Key to Poverty Eradication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 7 (Xinhua) -- To safeguard world peace and
establish a favorable external environment is essential for
eradicating poverty and advancing the cause of women, said Chinese
Ambassador Qiao Zonghuai here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Warfare is the source of all evils. It not only causes
casualties, but also squanders considerable amount of money and
brings the society backward," Qiao said when delivering a speech
at the high-level segment of the 1999 substantive meeting of the
United Nations' Economic and Social Council (ECOSOC).
</P>
<P>
He said that the war staged not long ago in the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia is one typical example confirming that
women are usually the most direct victims of war and armed
conflicts.
</P>
<P>
"War makes them homeless, deprives them of their family members,
and more seriously, reduces them into poverty and their right to
subsistence," Qiao pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that a peaceful environment is the most fundamental
safeguard for advancing the cause of women and eradicating poverty.
Responsible nations or country blocs should never, with their
strong forces, bully the weaker, nor use or threaten to use forces
to destroy world peace.
</P>
<P>
"Only under such circumstances could favorable conditions be
established for the international efforts to advance women and
eradicate poverty," Qiao said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
