<HEADLINE> Chinese Sun Shoots Crystal Palace to 2-1 Win over Guo'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese international defender Sun
Jihai received both applauds and boos for his powerful strike
which gave his English first-division club Crystal Palace a 2-1
win over China's Beijing Guo'an in a friendly Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Sun, who was transferred from China's Dalian Wanda to the
London club last summer, stroke the second goal of the visiting
side in the 56th minute.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Olympic player had a spectacular 60-minute
performance before walked out of the pitch in waves of applauds
and boos from the 10,000 fans in the Workers stadium.
</P>
<P>
"It feels good to score on Guo'an club's grass for the Crystal
Palace," Sun said. "I would be happier if I could score in Dalian.
"
</P>
<P>
Crystal Palace head coach Steve Copple was satisfied with
performances of Sun and Sun's country fellow Fan Zhiyi, a former
Shanghai Shenhua center back, who moved to England alongside with
Sun last season.
</P>
<P>
"They both played very well," Copple said. "Sun scored the goal,
and I was very pleased."
</P>
<P>
"This is our first game in eight weeks," he added.
</P>
<P>
Clinton Morrison opened the mark with a 33rd-minute header from
a Sun's cross, while Han Xu pulled one back for Guo'an five
minutes before the buzzer.
</P>
<P>
Crystal Palace will play Liaoning Fushun, another Chinese first-
division side, on Saturday. 
</P>
