<DOCNO> XIE19990707.0373 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, July 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India Wednesday rejected Pakistan's attempts to
link the Kargil conflict with the Kashmir issue.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Islamabad, Pakistan's capital, said
Pakistan could appeal to the Mujahideen to withdraw from the
Indian side of the Line of Control (LOC) if India promised to
solve the whole Kashmir issue.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Indian External Affairs Ministry said here
that his country also ruled out any move on its part to facilitate
the withdrawal of the "infiltrators" from the Indian side of the
LOC, saying, "They would have to find their own way out."
</P>
<P>
Briefing reporters here, he said, "We reject this linkage
completely." The military operations would continue till every
inch of Indian territory was cleared of the intruders, he further
said. (India-Pakistan-Kashmir)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KATHMANDU -- A cargo plane of the German Lufthansa Airlines
crashed Wednesday evening nine minutes after it took off from the
Tribhuvan International Airport here, but the fate of the five
persons aboard is unknown, the airport said.
</P>
<P>
An airport source said the plane hit a hill and was burning. He
said the fate of those on board was not clear. "It's difficult to
get alive," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said their nationalities are also not clear but four of them
may be Indian nationals. (Nepal-Plane Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The United Kingdom is to resume full diplomatic
relations with Libya after a break of 15 years, Foreign Secretary
Robin Cook told the House of Commons on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Britain cut its ties with Libya in 1984 after the shooting of
policewoman Yvonne Fletcher outside the Libyan embassy in London
during a protest against Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi.
</P>
<P>
Cook said Libya had agreed general responsibility for her death
and would help police find her killers and to compensate Fletcher'
s family.
</P>
<P>
"The two agreements we have secured open the way for us to
resume diplomatic relations with Libya," Cook said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, officials from the foreign office had said that
British ambassador could be back in Tripoli, the capital of Libya,
by the autumn. (Britain-Libya-Relations)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia and Belarus may sign a treaty next fall on the
establishment of a union state between them, Russian Prime
Minister Sergei Stepashin said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A program of steps to be taken in creating a union state must
be drafted simultaneously with the treaty in this month,
Stepashin told the Executive Council of the union of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The two sides do not essentially differ on the structure or
contents of the treaty, Stepashin said.
</P>
<P>
"Russia and Belarus are strategic allies. We will not change
this view," the Interfax news agency quoted Stepashin as saying.
</P>
<P>
"We are moving ever closer to becoming a unified state,"
Stepashin said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting followed Belarussian President Alexander
Lukashenko's complaint of Russia's slow pace in establishing the
union and threat to get closer to the West if Moscow does not
speed up.
</P>
<P>
The statements prompted a quick response from Moscow, with
Russian President Boris Yeltsin ordering the Stepashin cabinet to
do its best to enter the 21st century as a union state with
Belarus. (Russia-Belarus-Union) 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
