<HEADLINE> Cipollini Takes Fourth Leg of Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Italian sprinting ace Mario Cipollini
edged Germany's Erik Zabel to win the fourth stage of the Tour de
France in a photo finish from Laval in Blois, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The stage was won at a record pace averaging 50.355 kph (31.47
mph). The previous record was 49.417 kph (30.885 mph), according
to reports.
</P>
<P>
Third place went to Australian Stuart O'Grady. Fourth was Tom
Steels of Belgium, the winner of the last two stages.
</P>
<P>
Estonian Jann Kirsipuu retained the overall leader's yellow
jersey. He came in fifth on Wednesday. Endiem
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
