<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Stresses Trade Ties With China: Top Lawmaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 7 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Supreme Council Chairman
Alexandr Nikolayevich Tkachenko said here Wednesday that his
country will continue to advance its economic and trade ties with
China.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Chen Junsheng, vice chairman of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC),
Tkachenko said Ukraine and China could promote bilateral trade by
strengthening cooperation in science-technology, machine-building,
defense industry, agriculture, shipbuilding, aeronautics,
astronautics and other fields.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that both countries would exchange
experience in economic reforms. China's experience in
establishing special economic zones is very important for Ukraine,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Chen agreed with Tkachenko and expressed thanks to him for
Ukraine's support for China on Taiwan and Human Rights issues.
</P>
<P>
Chen, who arrived here Tuesday for a six-day visit to Ukraine,
will also meet other Ukrainian leaders during his visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
